WEBVTT

00:00:00.430 --> 00:00:20.430
This Qur'an guides us to the path of goodness, it guides us. Allah subhanahu wa sallam has sent it down, and the Messenger of Allah is our teacher, the Messenger of Allah is our teacher.

00:00:20.430 --> 00:00:22.430
Bismillah ar-Rahman ar-Rahim

00:00:43.430 --> 00:00:47.430
My dear brothers and sisters, Salamu alaykum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuh

00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:57.430
So we're going to be discussing the fourth hadith of Imam an-Nawawi's 40 hadith, and this is actually a very relevant hadith and there's a lot of lessons that need to be learned from this hadith.

00:00:57.430 --> 00:01:03.430
So let us start off with the very beginning of the hadith, where Imam an-Nawawi says

00:01:03.430 --> 00:01:22.430
So this hadith is narrated by Abdullah ibn Mas'ud and Abdullah ibn Mas'ud was one of the early companions that accepted Islam in Mecca.

00:01:22.430 --> 00:01:30.430
Now you'll notice that he starts off this hadith by saying that the Messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam and he is a sadiq al-masduq.

00:01:30.430 --> 00:01:43.430
The term a sadiq means he is the one that speaks the truth, and al-masduq it means the person whose honesty has been proven, whose honesty has been proven and legislated.

00:01:43.430 --> 00:01:52.430
Now why does Abdullah ibn Mas'ud start off with this disclaimer that he is the trustworthy one and his trustworthiness has been affirmed?

00:01:52.430 --> 00:02:00.430
The reason why Abdullah ibn Mas'ud starts off with this disclaimer is because of the content that is going to be coming into this hadith.

00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:09.430
As we know that when Islam first came the Messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam himself was unable to read and write and this was the case of the vast majority of people.

00:02:10.430 --> 00:02:17.430
So even in terms of progress, in terms of science and particularly medical studies, very little was discovered.

00:02:17.430 --> 00:02:29.430
And with the coming of Islam, science progressed very very quickly in terms of its theoretical knowledge because Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala revealed knowledge that was unknown to mankind at that time.

00:02:29.430 --> 00:02:33.430
And that was the knowledge of how the human being is formed.

00:02:33.430 --> 00:02:46.430
So if you look inside the very first verses of Surah Al-Mu'minun, you'll notice that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala discusses the concept of how the fetus is formed and what happens in the womb and the different stages of human life at that time.

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:53.430
And this is why Abdullah ibn Mas'ud radiAllahu anhu, he starts off with this disclaimer that he is a sadiq al-masduq.

00:02:53.430 --> 00:02:57.430
Can someone just ask the brothers who are talking in the back to please stay quiet inshallah?

00:02:57.430 --> 00:03:00.810
JazakAllah khayran.

00:03:00.810 --> 00:03:05.810
And this is why he gives this disclaimer that he is a sadiq al-masduq.

00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:10.810
Now what is the effect of this disclaimer in terms of aqidah, in terms of our faith?

00:03:10.810 --> 00:03:12.810
What effect does this have?

00:03:12.810 --> 00:03:14.810
It has a huge effect my dear brothers and sisters.

00:03:14.810 --> 00:03:21.810
And that effect is that anything the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam came with, it needs to be accepted.

00:03:21.810 --> 00:03:28.810
So anything that is authentically attributed to the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam, it cannot be rejected whatsoever.

00:03:29.810 --> 00:03:33.810
In surah al-hujurat, Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, he describes the believers.

00:03:33.810 --> 00:03:38.810
He says they are the ones that believe in Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala and the messenger.

00:03:40.810 --> 00:03:43.810
And then they have no doubt about this whatsoever.

00:03:43.810 --> 00:03:48.810
So anything that the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam came with or Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala said,

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:51.810
then it has to be accepted without a shadow of a doubt.

00:03:51.810 --> 00:03:53.810
So now a situation arises.

00:03:53.810 --> 00:03:57.810
What if there is a hadith that is in contradiction?

00:03:57.810 --> 00:03:59.810
And it's in contradiction to two things.

00:03:59.810 --> 00:04:01.810
Number one, with another hadith.

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:04.810
And number two, with science.

00:04:04.810 --> 00:04:10.810
So let's talk about in terms of hadith being in contradiction to other revelations.

00:04:10.810 --> 00:04:13.810
So we'll make it general, not just other hadith, but other revelations.

00:04:13.810 --> 00:04:19.810
Whether it is the Quran or the Sunnah, how do you deal with contradictions between different forms of revelation?

00:04:19.810 --> 00:04:23.810
Imam ibn Khuzaymah rahimahu Allah, he died in the year 311.

00:04:23.810 --> 00:04:27.810
He died in the year 311 and he made a very pompous claim.

00:04:27.810 --> 00:04:35.810
And that claim was that anyone that ever finds any contradiction in revelation between either one hadith or another

00:04:35.810 --> 00:04:38.810
or one hadith in the Quran, then let him bring it to me.

00:04:38.810 --> 00:04:42.810
Then let him bring it to me and I will reconcile it for him.

00:04:42.810 --> 00:04:44.810
And I will reconcile it for him.

00:04:44.810 --> 00:04:50.810
So the point that he was trying to make is that there is not going to be any contradiction in revelation

00:04:50.810 --> 00:04:53.810
because the source of that revelation is one.

00:04:53.810 --> 00:04:55.810
That source of revelation is one.

00:04:55.810 --> 00:05:00.810
So what are possible reasons that one may find an apparent contradiction?

00:05:00.810 --> 00:05:02.810
Because it's not going to be a real contradiction.

00:05:02.810 --> 00:05:05.810
But what are reasons that a person might find an apparent contradiction?

00:05:05.810 --> 00:05:08.810
And you're going to find three main reasons for that.

00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:10.810
Three main reasons for that.

00:05:10.810 --> 00:05:15.810
Reason number one is that it is not authentically established.

00:05:15.810 --> 00:05:21.810
So particularly when it comes to a hadith, you will find some hadith that may contradict one another.

00:05:21.810 --> 00:05:24.810
But some of them are authentic, others of them are not.

00:05:24.810 --> 00:05:28.810
And if something is inauthentic, then obviously it cannot be used as a proof.

00:05:28.810 --> 00:05:31.810
It cannot be used as a proof.

00:05:31.810 --> 00:05:36.810
A second reason why you may find contradiction, apparent contradiction between revelation

00:05:36.810 --> 00:05:41.810
is the concept of nasikh and mansukh, is the concept of abrogation.

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:44.810
So Islam came as a very practical religion.

00:05:44.810 --> 00:05:50.810
And that being said, there are certain things that were revealed gradually.

00:05:50.810 --> 00:05:52.810
They weren't revealed all at one time.

00:05:52.810 --> 00:05:55.810
The easiest example of this is that of alcohol.

00:05:55.810 --> 00:06:00.810
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, when He prohibited alcohol, it was prohibited in three main stages.

00:06:00.810 --> 00:06:03.810
It was prohibited in three main stages.

00:06:03.810 --> 00:06:07.810
Until Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala finally prohibited alcohol altogether.

00:06:07.810 --> 00:06:11.810
So that is a second reason why a person may find an apparent contradiction.

00:06:11.810 --> 00:06:13.810
But in reality, it isn't a contradiction.

00:06:13.810 --> 00:06:19.810
It's just that something has abrogated the command or has abrogated the ruling.

00:06:19.810 --> 00:06:23.810
The third reason why a person may find a contradiction.

00:06:23.810 --> 00:06:32.810
And that is that in reality, that concept or that point is not from the messenger of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala himself.

00:06:32.810 --> 00:06:35.810
But from a sahabi. It's from a sahabi.

00:06:35.810 --> 00:06:38.810
So when the sahabi or the person narrating the hadith,

00:06:38.810 --> 00:06:43.810
he actually introduces something from himself into the hadith itself.

00:06:43.810 --> 00:06:48.810
And the reason why I mention this one in particular is because this is something we're going to see in this hadith.

00:06:48.810 --> 00:06:55.810
Where Abdullah bin Mas'ud radiAllahu anhu, he introduced something from himself to explain something from the hadith.

00:06:55.810 --> 00:06:57.810
To explain something from the hadith.

00:06:57.810 --> 00:07:00.810
So we need to find out that, yes, even if it is authentic,

00:07:00.810 --> 00:07:03.810
are these truly the words of the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam?

00:07:03.810 --> 00:07:07.810
Or is there something introduced from the sahabi himself?

00:07:07.810 --> 00:07:10.810
From the sahabi himself.

00:07:10.810 --> 00:07:14.810
A fourth reason that you will find apparent contradiction.

00:07:14.810 --> 00:07:19.810
And that is particularly when it comes to the hadith as opposed to the Quran.

00:07:19.810 --> 00:07:22.810
The Quran is preserved in wording and in meaning.

00:07:22.810 --> 00:07:25.810
Meaning that the wording of the Quran will never change.

00:07:25.810 --> 00:07:28.810
The meaning of the Quran will never change.

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:31.810
Whereas the hadith of the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:07:31.810 --> 00:07:35.810
they are preserved in meaning and not necessarily in wording.

00:07:35.810 --> 00:07:37.810
Meaning that the sahaba radiAllahu anhu,

00:07:37.810 --> 00:07:42.810
they used to take the luxury that if they did not remember the word,

00:07:42.810 --> 00:07:45.810
they would use a term that was synonymous with that term.

00:07:45.810 --> 00:07:49.810
So as long as the meaning was preserved, they didn't have a problem narrating the hadith.

00:07:49.810 --> 00:07:53.810
And sometimes a person or a sahabi or the person narrating the hadith

00:07:53.810 --> 00:07:56.810
may use a term that is not truly synonymous

00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:59.810
and that is what causes the contradiction.

00:07:59.810 --> 00:08:01.810
And that is what causes the contradiction.

00:08:01.810 --> 00:08:03.810
So those are four primary reasons.

00:08:03.810 --> 00:08:07.810
And the scholars have listed up to seven, some of them even up to ten,

00:08:07.810 --> 00:08:10.810
different reasons why a person may find an apparent contradiction.

00:08:10.810 --> 00:08:13.810
But in reality it will not be a contradiction.

00:08:13.810 --> 00:08:15.810
Now we get to issue number two.

00:08:15.810 --> 00:08:19.810
And that is what if an individual finds an apparent contradiction

00:08:19.810 --> 00:08:24.810
between science and revelation.

00:08:24.810 --> 00:08:27.810
And rather than using the term science, we're going to use the term intellect.

00:08:27.810 --> 00:08:30.810
Because science is a product of our intellects.

00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:32.810
And this is the term that the earlier scholars used.

00:08:32.810 --> 00:08:35.810
And one of the great, I guess, thesis is, if you want to call it that,

00:08:35.810 --> 00:08:37.810
that was written on this subject,

00:08:37.810 --> 00:08:40.810
was written by Shaykh al-Islam Ibn Taymiyyah rahimahu Allah.

00:08:40.810 --> 00:08:41.810
It was called,

00:08:43.810 --> 00:08:47.810
that removing all of the doubts relating to the contradictions

00:08:47.810 --> 00:08:50.810
between intellect and revelation.

00:08:50.810 --> 00:08:53.810
So the first thing that's important to understand over here

00:08:53.810 --> 00:08:58.810
is that the source of revelation and the creator of the intellect,

00:08:58.810 --> 00:09:00.810
again, is one and the same.

00:09:00.810 --> 00:09:03.810
So if they are both from the creator,

00:09:03.810 --> 00:09:05.810
then there shouldn't be any contradiction.

00:09:05.810 --> 00:09:07.810
Then there shouldn't be any contradiction.

00:09:07.810 --> 00:09:09.810
So where will the contradiction come from?

00:09:09.810 --> 00:09:12.810
Where will the contradiction come from?

00:09:12.810 --> 00:09:16.810
The contradiction will come from two main cases in this situation.

00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:21.810
Case number one is that there is a flaw in the understanding.

00:09:21.810 --> 00:09:23.810
There is a flaw in the understanding.

00:09:23.810 --> 00:09:25.810
A flaw in the logic.

00:09:25.810 --> 00:09:27.810
So logical deduction that mankind comes to,

00:09:27.810 --> 00:09:29.810
that's where the flaw is.

00:09:29.810 --> 00:09:32.810
Whereas the text within of itself is perfectly fine,

00:09:32.810 --> 00:09:35.810
and there's no issue with it whatsoever.

00:09:35.810 --> 00:09:38.810
A second reason that actually,

00:09:38.810 --> 00:09:40.810
sticking to the first reason first,

00:09:40.810 --> 00:09:42.810
another thing related to reason number one is that

00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:46.810
there's a flaw in logic or a flaw in the deduction,

00:09:46.810 --> 00:09:50.810
is that this can also be applied to progress in science.

00:09:50.810 --> 00:09:53.810
So as science progresses and as science develops,

00:09:53.810 --> 00:09:55.810
obviously theories will change, right?

00:09:55.810 --> 00:09:58.810
And as what was known as a fact 50 years ago

00:09:58.810 --> 00:10:00.810
is no longer considered a fact now,

00:10:00.810 --> 00:10:02.810
because our understanding of the world,

00:10:02.810 --> 00:10:04.810
our understanding of science is developing.

00:10:04.810 --> 00:10:06.810
So this will go under category number one.

00:10:06.810 --> 00:10:09.810
Then the second reason why a person may find a contradiction

00:10:09.810 --> 00:10:13.810
or an apparent contradiction between intellect and revelation,

00:10:13.810 --> 00:10:16.810
then this is from one of the points from part number one,

00:10:16.810 --> 00:10:21.810
and that is that perhaps there is the narration

00:10:21.810 --> 00:10:23.810
that is being referred to is inauthentic.

00:10:23.810 --> 00:10:28.810
Perhaps the narration that is being referred to is inauthentic.

00:10:28.810 --> 00:10:31.810
So those are generally how the scholars address

00:10:31.810 --> 00:10:33.810
the issue of contradiction between revelation

00:10:33.810 --> 00:10:38.810
and contradiction between science and intellect within themselves.

00:10:38.810 --> 00:10:41.810
Two people that paid a lot of attention to this

00:10:41.810 --> 00:10:44.810
from the people of the past was Ibn Taymiyyah Rahimullah

00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:46.810
in his thesis, Dhar Tahrid al-Aqal al-Naqal.

00:10:46.810 --> 00:10:49.810
And in our time, someone who paid more close attention

00:10:49.810 --> 00:10:51.810
to the concept of revelation within of itself

00:10:51.810 --> 00:10:53.810
was Shaykh Muhammad Amin al-Shanqiti.

00:10:53.810 --> 00:10:56.810
So Shaykh Muhammad Amin al-Shanqiti, Rahimahu Allah Ta'ala,

00:10:56.810 --> 00:10:59.810
what he did was he took all of the verses

00:10:59.810 --> 00:11:02.810
and all of the hadith that people had a problem with.

00:11:02.810 --> 00:11:05.810
So the hadith that the sun bows down

00:11:05.810 --> 00:11:08.810
to the Arsh of Allah Subhanahu wa Ta'ala every day

00:11:08.810 --> 00:11:10.810
as it rises and sets.

00:11:10.810 --> 00:11:13.810
And the hadith that if one part of the wing of the fly

00:11:13.810 --> 00:11:15.810
has the poison in it, then the other part of the wing

00:11:15.810 --> 00:11:17.810
has the cure in it.

00:11:17.810 --> 00:11:19.810
All these narrations people will have a problem with.

00:11:19.810 --> 00:11:21.810
They're like, how do we understand these things?

00:11:21.810 --> 00:11:23.810
How can this actually be true?

00:11:23.810 --> 00:11:25.810
And Shaykh Muhammad Amin al-Shanqiti, he has a book

00:11:25.810 --> 00:11:28.810
that he compiled dealing with all the verses

00:11:28.810 --> 00:11:31.810
and the hadith that are problematic on the apparent.

00:11:31.810 --> 00:11:35.810
And you can research more about that book, bi'idhnillah ta'ala.

00:11:35.810 --> 00:11:37.810
So that is why Abdullah ibn Mas'ud radiAllahu anhu

00:11:37.810 --> 00:11:40.810
started off with this disclaimer that

00:11:40.810 --> 00:11:43.810
he is al-sadiq al-masduq, that anything that comes

00:11:43.810 --> 00:11:45.810
from the messenger of Allah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:11:45.810 --> 00:11:47.810
his truthfulness, his trustworthiness

00:11:47.810 --> 00:11:49.810
has already been established.

00:11:49.810 --> 00:11:52.810
So you cannot deny it, because to doubt it

00:11:52.810 --> 00:11:54.810
or to deny it, then this would be disbelief.

00:11:54.810 --> 00:11:56.810
If you were to doubt it or to deny it,

00:11:56.810 --> 00:11:59.810
then this would be disbelief.

00:11:59.810 --> 00:12:01.810
Now let's actually get into the actual text

00:12:01.810 --> 00:12:03.810
of the hadith itself.

00:12:03.810 --> 00:12:05.810
So we're going to just say it in English

00:12:05.810 --> 00:12:07.810
with the exception of one part, bi'idhnillah ta'ala.

00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:08.810
So he says,

00:12:18.810 --> 00:12:21.810
So the messenger of Allah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:12:21.810 --> 00:12:24.810
he talks about the very concept

00:12:24.810 --> 00:12:26.810
of how human beings are developed.

00:12:26.810 --> 00:12:29.810
And this is one of the scientific miracles of the Quran.

00:12:29.810 --> 00:12:31.810
So obviously this knowledge was not known

00:12:31.810 --> 00:12:34.810
at the time of the messenger of Allah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:12:34.810 --> 00:12:36.810
not with the doctors, not with the Muslims,

00:12:36.810 --> 00:12:38.810
not with the previous religions,

00:12:38.810 --> 00:12:41.810
but this is one of the things that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:41.810 --> 00:12:44.810
revealed to prove that this was a revelation

00:12:44.810 --> 00:12:46.810
from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala himself.

00:12:46.810 --> 00:12:48.810
And this brings us to a topic of,

00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:51.810
one of the criticisms that is made against the Quran

00:12:51.810 --> 00:12:53.810
is a criticism known as Hegerism.

00:12:53.810 --> 00:12:55.810
And what Hegerism actually is,

00:12:55.810 --> 00:12:59.810
is it is an accusation against the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:12:59.810 --> 00:13:03.810
that he compiled the Quran from previous sources.

00:13:03.810 --> 00:13:05.810
So they say that when the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:13:05.810 --> 00:13:08.810
went to go see Waraqa ibn Naufal,

00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:10.810
that's when he had knowledge of the Bible.

00:13:10.810 --> 00:13:13.810
So he took some of the Bible and made it into the Quran.

00:13:13.810 --> 00:13:16.810
And when the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam came to Medina,

00:13:16.810 --> 00:13:19.810
he had interaction with the Jews of Medina,

00:13:19.810 --> 00:13:22.810
and he took some of the Torah

00:13:22.810 --> 00:13:24.810
and he put that into the Quran as well.

00:13:24.810 --> 00:13:27.810
And that is how the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam put the Quran together.

00:13:27.810 --> 00:13:30.810
And that is in just brief summary what Hegerism actually is.

00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:34.810
Now, one of the simplest ways to refute that concept

00:13:34.810 --> 00:13:39.810
is how about that material that isn't found inside of the previous scriptures.

00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:41.810
And this is a clear example of it.

00:13:41.810 --> 00:13:45.810
That the form of how human beings were formed and developed

00:13:45.810 --> 00:13:47.810
is not mentioned in any of the previous scriptures.

00:13:47.810 --> 00:13:50.810
But rather this is something that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:50.810 --> 00:13:52.810
revealed in the Quran itself.

00:13:52.810 --> 00:13:55.810
And something like this in our day and age,

00:13:55.810 --> 00:13:57.810
it may not uplift our Iman

00:13:57.810 --> 00:14:00.810
because alhamdulillah science has now reached that level

00:14:00.810 --> 00:14:02.810
where we understand these things.

00:14:02.810 --> 00:14:04.810
In fact, so much so that, you know,

00:14:04.810 --> 00:14:06.810
when a couple who is expecting a baby,

00:14:06.810 --> 00:14:08.810
they go to a doctor now,

00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:10.810
even before the baby is born they can tell

00:14:10.810 --> 00:14:12.810
what the gender is.

00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:14.810
And I'm not just talking about, you know,

00:14:14.810 --> 00:14:16.810
just a simple...

00:14:16.810 --> 00:14:18.810
What's the word called?

00:14:18.810 --> 00:14:20.810
Not even the ultrasound.

00:14:20.810 --> 00:14:23.810
It's not the ultrasound. I'm thinking of a different word.

00:14:23.810 --> 00:14:25.810
But the simple version of it is the ultrasound.

00:14:25.810 --> 00:14:28.810
But even the ultrasound has been taken to a next level.

00:14:28.810 --> 00:14:30.810
Like the ultrasound is usually just in 2D form

00:14:30.810 --> 00:14:31.810
and it's like black and white.

00:14:31.810 --> 00:14:33.810
But now technology has come to such a level

00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:36.810
it actually creates a 3D image of the baby

00:14:36.810 --> 00:14:39.810
and you can see a 3D image of the baby

00:14:39.810 --> 00:14:41.810
while it's inside the mother's womb.

00:14:41.810 --> 00:14:43.810
And that is how far technology has come.

00:14:43.810 --> 00:14:45.810
So in our day and age it may not uplift our spirits

00:14:45.810 --> 00:14:47.810
but you can imagine for the Bedouin man

00:14:47.810 --> 00:14:50.810
that has no understanding of how, you know,

00:14:50.810 --> 00:14:51.810
the human being is developed.

00:14:51.810 --> 00:14:53.810
Or even the philosopher at that time.

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:55.810
If you look at, you know,

00:14:55.810 --> 00:14:57.810
Aristotelian philosophy and how they perceived

00:14:57.810 --> 00:14:59.810
the development of human being,

00:14:59.810 --> 00:15:01.810
they just considered it, you know,

00:15:01.810 --> 00:15:04.810
one tiny, tiny human being.

00:15:04.810 --> 00:15:06.810
And that tiny human being over time

00:15:06.810 --> 00:15:08.810
gradually grew inside the mother's stomach

00:15:08.810 --> 00:15:10.810
and that's what came out.

