00:36:02.340 --> 00:36:04.340
will happen. That's what it means.

00:36:04.340 --> 00:36:06.340
When Allah wills something, it will happen.

00:36:06.340 --> 00:36:08.340
You can try your utmost best

00:36:08.340 --> 00:36:10.340
to prevent it from happening. Try

00:36:10.340 --> 00:36:12.340
to avoid it as much as you possibly can

00:36:12.340 --> 00:36:14.340
but there's nothing you can do to

00:36:14.340 --> 00:36:16.340
get out of it. Then the second

00:36:16.340 --> 00:36:18.340
thing is the irada of Allah

00:36:18.340 --> 00:36:20.340
subhanahu wa ta'ala. And the irada

00:36:20.340 --> 00:36:22.340
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala is of two types.

00:36:22.340 --> 00:36:24.340
And that is al-qawniyyah

00:36:24.340 --> 00:36:26.340
and al-shariyyah. The qawniyyah

00:36:26.340 --> 00:36:28.340
is referring to the matters

00:36:28.340 --> 00:36:30.340
of this world. That Allah wants

00:36:30.340 --> 00:36:32.340
the sun to set. Allah

00:36:32.340 --> 00:36:34.340
wants the moon and stars to come

00:36:34.340 --> 00:36:36.340
out. Allah wants it to

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:38.340
rain. So this has nothing to do with us

00:36:38.340 --> 00:36:40.340
but this has to do with the external

00:36:40.340 --> 00:36:42.340
creation. Right?

00:36:42.340 --> 00:36:44.340
So there's no element of reward

00:36:44.340 --> 00:36:46.340
or punishment related to

00:36:46.340 --> 00:36:48.340
al-irada al-qawniyyah.

00:36:48.340 --> 00:36:50.340
That you will not be questioned about when the sun

00:36:50.340 --> 00:36:52.340
set and when it rose and when the rain

00:36:52.340 --> 00:36:54.340
came down. You're not going to be questioned about that.

00:36:54.340 --> 00:36:56.340
However the second type of

00:36:56.340 --> 00:36:58.340
wanting which is al-irada

00:36:58.340 --> 00:37:00.340
al-shariyyah. And these are the things

00:37:00.340 --> 00:37:02.340
that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala wants

00:37:02.340 --> 00:37:04.340
from us. But we have

00:37:04.340 --> 00:37:06.340
the free will to do them or not.

00:37:06.340 --> 00:37:08.340
And this is what we will be

00:37:08.340 --> 00:37:10.340
judged upon. So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:37:10.340 --> 00:37:12.340
gave us the commandment to pray.

00:37:12.340 --> 00:37:14.340
We will be judged upon did we pray or

00:37:14.340 --> 00:37:16.340
not. Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala told us to be

00:37:16.340 --> 00:37:18.340
good to our parents. We will be

00:37:18.340 --> 00:37:20.340
questioned about were we good to our parents

00:37:20.340 --> 00:37:22.340
or not. So this is the irada

00:37:22.340 --> 00:37:24.340
al-shariyyah. And this is where a lot of

00:37:24.340 --> 00:37:26.340
people make a mistake that hey if Allah

00:37:26.340 --> 00:37:28.340
has destined everything. He wants

00:37:28.340 --> 00:37:30.340
me to be good. I will be good.

00:37:30.340 --> 00:37:32.340
Right? The mistake is in this

00:37:32.340 --> 00:37:34.340
third level over here. That do not

00:37:34.340 --> 00:37:36.340
confuse the mashia of Allah subhanahu

00:37:36.340 --> 00:37:38.340
wa ta'ala with the irada

00:37:38.340 --> 00:37:40.340
al-shariyyah of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:37:40.340 --> 00:37:42.340
So what Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala will force into

00:37:42.340 --> 00:37:44.340
happening is not the same thing

00:37:44.340 --> 00:37:46.340
as what Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:37:46.340 --> 00:37:48.340
expects from you or wants you

00:37:48.340 --> 00:37:50.340
to do in your life.

00:37:50.340 --> 00:37:52.340
And then the fourth and last level of qadr

00:37:52.340 --> 00:37:54.340
we said is that all of

00:37:54.340 --> 00:37:56.340
our actions are created.

00:37:56.340 --> 00:37:58.340
However, the goodness of

00:37:58.340 --> 00:38:00.340
them, then that is a result from

00:38:00.340 --> 00:38:02.340
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala. Whereas

00:38:02.340 --> 00:38:04.340
the bad of them, then

00:38:04.340 --> 00:38:06.340
this is a result of our own deeds.

00:38:06.340 --> 00:38:08.340
This is a result of our own deeds and our

00:38:08.340 --> 00:38:10.340
own doing. And the clearest

00:38:10.340 --> 00:38:12.340
indication of this as the Prophet

00:38:12.340 --> 00:38:14.340
salallahu alayhi wasalam made it very

00:38:14.340 --> 00:38:16.340
very clear.

00:38:16.340 --> 00:38:18.340
That when he

00:38:18.340 --> 00:38:20.340
used to make dua to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:38:20.340 --> 00:38:22.340
he used to say, and no evil is

00:38:22.340 --> 00:38:24.340
attributed to you. And Allah

00:38:24.340 --> 00:38:26.340
subhanahu wa ta'ala, he tells us in the Quran

00:38:26.340 --> 00:38:28.340
ظهر الفساد في البر والبحر

00:38:28.340 --> 00:38:30.340
بما كسبت

00:38:30.340 --> 00:38:32.340
أيدي الناس. That

00:38:32.340 --> 00:38:34.340
fasad, evil and wickedness

00:38:34.340 --> 00:38:36.340
has become present in this

00:38:36.340 --> 00:38:38.340
world as a result

00:38:38.340 --> 00:38:40.340
not of Allah's will but because of

00:38:40.340 --> 00:38:42.340
the evil actions that mankind

00:38:42.340 --> 00:38:44.340
themselves used to do. So evil is

00:38:44.340 --> 00:38:46.340
attributed to man and it is never

00:38:46.340 --> 00:38:48.340
attributed to Allah subhanahu

00:38:48.340 --> 00:38:50.340
wa ta'ala. Now

00:38:50.340 --> 00:38:52.340
as a sub-point related to this,

00:38:52.340 --> 00:38:54.340
this relates to the concept of

00:38:54.340 --> 00:38:56.340
good and evil in Islam.

00:38:56.340 --> 00:38:58.340
That from a Muslim's perspective, is there

00:38:58.340 --> 00:39:00.340
such a thing as absolute

00:39:00.340 --> 00:39:02.340
complete evil?

00:39:02.340 --> 00:39:04.340
And the answer to that is no.

00:39:04.340 --> 00:39:06.340
There is nothing that Allah subhanahu

00:39:06.340 --> 00:39:08.340
wa ta'ala has created that is

00:39:08.340 --> 00:39:10.340
100% absolute

00:39:10.340 --> 00:39:12.340
evil. And

00:39:12.340 --> 00:39:14.340
when my teacher was explaining

00:39:14.340 --> 00:39:16.340
this, he used a funny joke, I don't know

00:39:16.340 --> 00:39:18.340
since this is being recorded and live, how well it's

00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:20.340
going to work, but he said there's nothing that's 100%

00:39:20.340 --> 00:39:22.340
absolute pure evil,

00:39:22.340 --> 00:39:24.340
not even your mother-in-law.

00:39:24.340 --> 00:39:26.340
That's what he said.

00:39:26.340 --> 00:39:28.340
So I'm just narrating it as he said it.

00:39:28.340 --> 00:39:30.340
So even

00:39:30.340 --> 00:39:32.340
if you were to look at the concept of

00:39:32.340 --> 00:39:34.340
iblis and shaitan, is iblis

00:39:34.340 --> 00:39:36.340
and shaitan 100%

00:39:36.340 --> 00:39:38.340
pure evil? And the answer

00:39:38.340 --> 00:39:40.340
to that is from our perspective, no

00:39:40.340 --> 00:39:42.340
that is not the case. How so?

00:39:42.340 --> 00:39:44.340
The reason that is, my dear brothers and

00:39:44.340 --> 00:39:46.340
sisters, because

00:39:46.340 --> 00:39:48.340
if iblis and shaitan did not exist,

00:39:48.340 --> 00:39:50.340
then we would have no temptations

00:39:50.340 --> 00:39:52.340
to fight off, with which we would not

00:39:52.340 --> 00:39:54.340
incur any good deeds. If iblis

00:39:54.340 --> 00:39:56.340
and shaitan did not exist, we would not

00:39:56.340 --> 00:39:58.340
say a'oodhu billahi min shaitani

00:39:58.340 --> 00:40:00.340
ar-rajim and get rewarded

00:40:00.340 --> 00:40:02.340
for that act. So it is through the

00:40:02.340 --> 00:40:04.340
presence of iblis that these

00:40:04.340 --> 00:40:06.340
good deeds are possibly done.

00:40:06.340 --> 00:40:08.340
Had iblis not existed, then those

00:40:08.340 --> 00:40:10.340
deeds could not have been

00:40:10.340 --> 00:40:12.340
done. So that in summary

00:40:12.340 --> 00:40:14.340
is the portion of the hadith

00:40:14.340 --> 00:40:16.340
of the wording of the messenger of Allah sallallahu alaihi

00:40:16.340 --> 00:40:18.340
wa sallam. The next part of

00:40:18.340 --> 00:40:20.340
this narration, they are from the words

00:40:20.340 --> 00:40:22.340
of Abdullah bin Mas'ud. They are from the words

00:40:22.340 --> 00:40:24.340
of Abdullah bin Mas'ud, and we'll go

00:40:24.340 --> 00:40:26.340
through it very quickly and briefly

00:40:26.340 --> 00:40:28.340
bi dhinnahi ta'ala. He says,

00:40:28.340 --> 00:40:30.340
I swear by Allah, and there is

00:40:30.340 --> 00:40:32.340
no god other than He, one of you

00:40:32.340 --> 00:40:34.340
may perform the deeds of the people of

00:40:34.340 --> 00:40:36.340
paradise till there is not an

00:40:36.340 --> 00:40:38.340
arm's length between Him and it.

00:40:38.340 --> 00:40:40.340
Then that which has been written

00:40:40.340 --> 00:40:42.340
will come forth, and He will become

00:40:42.340 --> 00:40:44.340
from the people of the hellfire.

00:40:44.340 --> 00:40:46.340
And one of you may perform the deeds of the

00:40:46.340 --> 00:40:48.340
people of the hellfire till there is not

00:40:48.340 --> 00:40:50.340
between Him and arm's length and it,

00:40:50.340 --> 00:40:52.340
then that which has been written will come forth

00:40:52.340 --> 00:40:54.340
and overtake Him, and He will become

00:40:54.340 --> 00:40:56.340
from the people of paradise and will

00:40:56.340 --> 00:40:58.340
enter into it.

00:40:58.340 --> 00:41:00.340
So now,

00:41:00.340 --> 00:41:02.340
this is from the statements of

00:41:02.340 --> 00:41:04.340
Abdullah bin Mas'ud radiallahu

00:41:04.340 --> 00:41:06.340
anhu. And he

00:41:06.340 --> 00:41:08.340
starts off by swearing, by taking an oath

00:41:08.340 --> 00:41:10.340
by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, and this is

00:41:10.340 --> 00:41:12.340
a technique that is used to make a

00:41:12.340 --> 00:41:14.340
person believe. So a person says

00:41:14.340 --> 00:41:16.340
something, you know, I will do something

00:41:16.340 --> 00:41:18.340
and, you know,

00:41:18.340 --> 00:41:20.340
you might not believe them, but when the person says

00:41:20.340 --> 00:41:22.340
wallahi I will do it, you

00:41:22.340 --> 00:41:24.340
know, you take it more seriously. You think a person

00:41:24.340 --> 00:41:26.340
is more dedicated that they're swearing by Allah.

00:41:26.340 --> 00:41:28.340
Right? Unless, actually I don't

00:41:28.340 --> 00:41:30.340
want to insult the Somalis here, but if they

00:41:30.340 --> 00:41:32.340
say it then it has a different meaning altogether.

00:41:32.340 --> 00:41:34.340
No offense, inshallah.

00:41:34.340 --> 00:41:36.340
So a person takes an

00:41:36.340 --> 00:41:38.340
oath and that is for the sake of emphasis

00:41:38.340 --> 00:41:40.340
that look, this is really how it is

00:41:40.340 --> 00:41:42.340
to make people have conviction and belief

00:41:42.340 --> 00:41:44.340
in this. Now the reason

00:41:44.340 --> 00:41:46.340
why this is accepted as a part of

00:41:46.340 --> 00:41:48.340
the hadith, this is the reason why this is accepted

00:41:48.340 --> 00:41:50.340
as a part of hadith. This is

00:41:50.340 --> 00:41:52.340
one of the principles of the science of hadith

00:41:52.340 --> 00:41:54.340
that if a sahabi ever

00:41:54.340 --> 00:41:56.340
speaks about a matter of the unseen,

00:41:56.340 --> 00:41:58.340
even though it is not a

00:41:58.340 --> 00:42:00.340
hadith, it takes the ruling of a hadith.

00:42:00.340 --> 00:42:02.340
It takes the ruling of the words of the messenger

00:42:02.340 --> 00:42:04.340
of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam, because

00:42:04.340 --> 00:42:06.340
he couldn't have known this subject matter

00:42:06.340 --> 00:42:08.340
had it not been for the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi

00:42:08.340 --> 00:42:10.340
wasallam. And that is why this portion

00:42:10.340 --> 00:42:12.340
of the hadith, even though it is from the words

00:42:12.340 --> 00:42:14.340
of Abdullah bin Mas'ud radiAllahu

00:42:14.340 --> 00:42:16.340
anhu, it takes the ruling of a hadith

00:42:16.340 --> 00:42:18.340
because he couldn't have known this other

00:42:18.340 --> 00:42:20.340
than through the messenger of Allah.

00:42:20.340 --> 00:42:22.340
And this is further proven through narrations of Bukhari

00:42:22.340 --> 00:42:24.340
and Muslim that the messenger of Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:42:24.340 --> 00:42:26.340
made similar statements to this.

00:42:26.340 --> 00:42:28.340
And that is that a person will do

00:42:28.340 --> 00:42:30.340
the actions of the people of paradise

00:42:30.340 --> 00:42:32.340
until Qadr overtakes him

00:42:32.340 --> 00:42:34.340
and then he goes to the hellfire.

00:42:34.340 --> 00:42:36.340
And vice versa, the opposite

00:42:36.340 --> 00:42:38.340
as well. Now how do

00:42:38.340 --> 00:42:40.340
we explain this subject matter?

00:42:40.340 --> 00:42:42.340
How do we explain this subject matter?

00:42:42.340 --> 00:42:44.340
That how is it fair that a person does

00:42:44.340 --> 00:42:46.340
the actions of the people of Jannah

00:42:46.340 --> 00:42:48.340
and then all of a sudden Qadr overtakes him

00:42:48.340 --> 00:42:50.340
and he is thrown into the

00:42:50.340 --> 00:42:52.340
hellfire. The way we explain

00:42:52.340 --> 00:42:54.340
this is that we have a simple

00:42:54.340 --> 00:42:56.340
principle in hadith. And this

00:42:56.340 --> 00:42:58.340
is a foundation that you should develop

00:42:58.340 --> 00:43:00.340
for your deen altogether.

00:43:00.340 --> 00:43:02.340
But if you want to understand anything in this

00:43:02.340 --> 00:43:04.340
religion, never take an

00:43:04.340 --> 00:43:06.340
isolated verse, never take an isolated

00:43:06.340 --> 00:43:08.340
hadith and try to develop

00:43:08.340 --> 00:43:10.340
a complete understanding.

00:43:10.340 --> 00:43:12.340
If you want to develop a complete understanding

00:43:12.340 --> 00:43:14.340
of a subject matter, you have to have

00:43:14.340 --> 00:43:16.340
all of the texts related to that

00:43:16.340 --> 00:43:18.340
subject matter. So when you combine

00:43:18.340 --> 00:43:20.340
all of the texts of

00:43:20.340 --> 00:43:22.340
hadith and Quran

00:43:22.340 --> 00:43:24.340
pertaining to Qadr, pertaining to this

00:43:24.340 --> 00:43:26.340
subject matter, you will find

00:43:26.340 --> 00:43:28.340
two things. Two things.

00:43:28.340 --> 00:43:30.340
Number one is that

00:43:30.340 --> 00:43:32.340
on the appearance, it seemed

00:43:32.340 --> 00:43:34.340
like this person was doing actions

00:43:34.340 --> 00:43:36.340
of the people of Paradise.

00:43:36.340 --> 00:43:38.340
But in reality, this person could

00:43:38.340 --> 00:43:40.340
have been a hypocrite. That he was hiding

00:43:40.340 --> 00:43:42.340
his hypocrisy and then he was thrown

00:43:42.340 --> 00:43:44.340
into the hellfire because it became apparent

00:43:44.340 --> 00:43:46.340
of his hypocrisy. And that

00:43:46.340 --> 00:43:48.340
is why that is the case.

00:43:48.340 --> 00:43:50.340
Right? So that is issue

00:43:50.340 --> 00:43:52.340
number one is that the person was

00:43:52.340 --> 00:43:54.340
a hypocrite. Number two

00:43:54.340 --> 00:43:56.340
is that maybe it did

00:43:56.340 --> 00:43:58.340
not reach the level of hypocrisy

00:43:58.340 --> 00:44:00.340
but there is no

00:44:00.340 --> 00:44:02.340
sincerity in his actions.

00:44:02.340 --> 00:44:04.340
So a person is doing all of these deeds

00:44:04.340 --> 00:44:06.340
that seem great, but in reality

00:44:06.340 --> 00:44:08.340
there is no sincerity in his

00:44:08.340 --> 00:44:10.340
actions. There is no sincerity in

00:44:10.340 --> 00:44:12.340
his actions. And that is why he is thrown

00:44:12.340 --> 00:44:14.340
into the hellfire. So that

00:44:14.340 --> 00:44:16.340
explains the first portion of the hadith.

00:44:16.340 --> 00:44:18.340
Where a person will seemingly be from the people

00:44:18.340 --> 00:44:20.340
of Paradise, but in reality isn't

00:44:20.340 --> 00:44:22.340
and then he is exposed for that.

00:44:22.340 --> 00:44:24.340
But how do we explain the second

00:44:24.340 --> 00:44:26.340
part of the hadith? Where a person

00:44:26.340 --> 00:44:28.340
seemingly does the actions

00:44:28.340 --> 00:44:30.340
of the people of the hellfire

00:44:30.340 --> 00:44:32.340
but in reality then

00:44:32.340 --> 00:44:34.340
Qadar overtakes him and he enters

00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:36.340
into Paradise. This too also

00:44:36.340 --> 00:44:38.340
has two perspectives to it.

00:44:38.340 --> 00:44:40.340
Number one is

00:44:40.340 --> 00:44:42.340
that this person has

00:44:42.340 --> 00:44:44.340
goodness in his heart, but

00:44:44.340 --> 00:44:46.340
because of his surroundings, he has just

00:44:46.340 --> 00:44:48.340
been completely led astray. So these

00:44:48.340 --> 00:44:50.340
are Muslims by definition

00:44:50.340 --> 00:44:52.340
that they were raised in a Muslim

00:44:52.340 --> 00:44:54.340
household. They have Muslim names

00:44:54.340 --> 00:44:56.340
but they know nothing about

00:44:56.340 --> 00:44:58.340
Islam whatsoever. However

00:44:58.340 --> 00:45:00.340
as soon as Islam comes

00:45:00.340 --> 00:45:02.340
to them, they'll accept it right away

00:45:02.340 --> 00:45:04.340
and that is what they die upon. And this

00:45:04.340 --> 00:45:06.340
is what you see some of the sahabah radiAllahu anhu

00:45:06.340 --> 00:45:08.340
they accepted Islam, they went onto

00:45:08.340 --> 00:45:10.340
the battlefield and they died right away and they

00:45:10.340 --> 00:45:12.340
were guaranteed Paradise. Because they had that goodness

00:45:12.340 --> 00:45:14.340
their fitra was still intact.

00:45:14.340 --> 00:45:16.340
So as soon as Islam came

00:45:16.340 --> 00:45:18.340
then all of a sudden it was very easy for

00:45:18.340 --> 00:45:20.340
them to accept. Very easy for them

00:45:20.340 --> 00:45:22.340
to accept. And then there was a second

00:45:22.340 --> 00:45:24.340
approach that was taken, pertaining

00:45:24.340 --> 00:45:26.340
to the second part. And this is something that is important

00:45:26.340 --> 00:45:28.340
to know as well. Our predecessors

00:45:28.340 --> 00:45:30.340
when they spoke about Qadar

00:45:30.340 --> 00:45:32.340
they had two important principles

00:45:32.340 --> 00:45:34.340
relating to it. And this is what I want to conclude

00:45:34.340 --> 00:45:36.340
with. Number one

00:45:36.340 --> 00:45:38.340
is that Qadar sirrullah.

00:45:38.340 --> 00:45:40.340
It is the secret of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:45:40.340 --> 00:45:42.340
And the secret of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:45:42.340 --> 00:45:44.340
will not truly be understood.

00:45:44.340 --> 00:45:46.340
Meaning that as much as you try to put

00:45:46.340 --> 00:45:48.340
your intellect to it, you're not truly

00:45:48.340 --> 00:45:50.340
going to understand how it works. Because

00:45:50.340 --> 00:45:52.340
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala is beyond space and

00:45:52.340 --> 00:45:54.340
time. He is the creator of the intellects

00:45:54.340 --> 00:45:56.340
and therefore anything we understand

00:45:56.340 --> 00:45:58.340
is restricted to space and time

00:45:58.340 --> 00:46:00.340
and is restricted to what our minds

00:46:00.340 --> 00:46:02.340
can possibly comprehend. And Allah

00:46:02.340 --> 00:46:04.340
subhanahu wa ta'ala is beyond

00:46:04.340 --> 00:46:06.340
that. Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala is

00:46:06.340 --> 00:46:08.340
beyond that. The second principle they

00:46:08.340 --> 00:46:10.340
had. That when it comes to matters of Qadar

00:46:10.340 --> 00:46:12.340
pass it just as

00:46:12.340 --> 00:46:14.340
it came. Meaning that ahadith

00:46:14.340 --> 00:46:16.340
pertaining to Qadar, ayat pertaining to Qadar

00:46:16.340 --> 00:46:18.340
don't try to dwell into them

00:46:18.340 --> 00:46:20.340
but rather just pass them on as

00:46:20.340 --> 00:46:22.340
they came. As long as you believe

00:46:22.340 --> 00:46:24.340
this is from the messenger of Allah, accept

00:46:24.340 --> 00:46:26.340
it at face value. Don't question it.

00:46:26.340 --> 00:46:28.340
Don't challenge it. Because at the end

00:46:28.340 --> 00:46:30.340
of the day, the messenger of Allah and

00:46:30.340 --> 00:46:32.340
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala won't lose anything.

00:46:32.340 --> 00:46:34.340
But you are the one that's going to lose out

00:46:34.340 --> 00:46:36.340
by trying to question it. And this is where

00:46:36.340 --> 00:46:38.340
submission and faith come into play.

00:46:38.340 --> 00:46:40.340
That your Islam is based

00:46:40.340 --> 00:46:42.340
upon submission to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:46:42.340 --> 00:46:44.340
And as long as you continuously

00:46:44.340 --> 00:46:46.340
submit to Allah, you will be guided.

00:46:46.340 --> 00:46:48.340
But the second you try to

00:46:48.340 --> 00:46:50.340
rebel and start questioning

00:46:50.340 --> 00:46:52.340
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, then that is

00:46:52.340 --> 00:46:54.340
when you have already begun to go

00:46:54.340 --> 00:46:56.340
astray. And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:46:56.340 --> 00:46:58.340
knows best. Now I'm

00:46:58.340 --> 00:47:00.340
assuming we have questions?

00:47:00.340 --> 00:47:02.340
People have questions? Okay. We'll leave

00:47:02.340 --> 00:47:04.340
five, ten minutes for questions

00:47:04.340 --> 00:47:06.340
with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala and we'll call it a night.

00:47:06.340 --> 00:47:08.340
Jazakumullahu khayran to everyone for sticking around.

00:47:08.340 --> 00:47:10.340
I know usually we conclude at nine, but I took

00:47:10.340 --> 00:47:12.340
the extra ten minutes to explain that. Anything

00:47:12.340 --> 00:47:14.340
that I've said that is correct is from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:47:14.340 --> 00:47:16.340
Anything that I've said that is incorrect

00:47:16.340 --> 00:47:18.340
is from myself and from shaytan.

00:47:18.340 --> 00:47:20.340
Subhanak allahum wa bihamdik ash-shahadu

00:47:20.340 --> 00:47:22.340
an la ilaha illa anta astaghfiruka

00:47:22.340 --> 00:47:24.340
wa at-tubu ilayk.
